{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17530626","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17530626"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T16:08:56+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T16:08:56+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14556"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14556","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14556"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.64,0.12,0.05,0.14]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7249"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"103855"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7249","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7249"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14556"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86280"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"26"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"88"},{"type":"tags","id":"302"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1177"},{"type":"tags","id":"1674"},{"type":"tags","id":"2118"},{"type":"tags","id":"2229"},{"type":"tags","id":"2551"},{"type":"tags","id":"2705"},{"type":"tags","id":"2706"},{"type":"tags","id":"4897"},{"type":"tags","id":"8118"},{"type":"tags","id":"12917"},{"type":"tags","id":"12919"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"17623"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17946"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17950"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18102"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35601"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35815"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"103855","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/103855"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 68-year-old man has been admitted to the Intensive Care Unit for 10 days following a severe traumatic brain injury. He has been intubated and mechanically ventilated since admission. He has no significant medical history and does not take any regular medications. On day 10, the patient develops a fever of 38.5\u00b0C and an increase in purulent tracheal secretions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears unwell with a pulse rate of 130/min, blood pressure 85/55 mmHg, respiratory rate 24/min (ventilator-triggered), SpO2 93% on FiO2 0.6, and temperature 38.5\u00b0C. Coarse crackles are heard in the right lower lung field. Chest X-ray shows a new infiltrate in the right lower lobe.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInvestigations reveal:\u003Cbr /\u003EWhite cell count: 16 \u00d7 10\u2079/L (4.0-11.0)\u003Cbr /\u003EC-reactive protein: 120 mg/L (\u0026lt;5)\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate empiric antibiotic regimen?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Azithromycin","Piperacillin-tazobactam","Amoxicillin-clavulanate","Cefepime","Ciprofloxacin and vancomycin"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with clinical features suggestive of ventilator-associated pneumonia (VAP), which is defined as pneumonia occurring more than 48 hours after endotracheal intubation. The patient has been intubated for 10 days, placing him at risk for late-onset VAP. Late onset VAP is associated with multidrug-resistant organisms, particularly \u003Cem\u003EPseudomonas aeruginosa\u003C/em\u003E and extended-spectrum beta-lactamase producing Enterobacteriaceae. The choice of empiric antibiotic therapy must provide broad-spectrum coverage against these resistant pathogens.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPiperacillin-tazobactam\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate first-line empiric therapy for VAP in patients at increased risk of \u003Cem\u003EPseudomonas aeruginosa\u003C/em\u003E infection. This beta-lactam/beta-lactamase inhibitor combination provides excellent coverage against \u003Cem\u003EPseudomonas\u003C/em\u003E and other gram-negative organisms commonly implicated in hospital-acquired pneumonia. The tazobactam component extends the spectrum to include many beta-lactamase producing organisms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECefepime\u003C/strong\u003E is an alternative anti-pseudomonal agent and would be appropriate for patients with penicillin allergies. However, piperacillin-tazobactam is generally preferred as first-line therapy due to its broader spectrum of activity and proven efficacy in VAP.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECiprofloxacin and vancomycin\u003C/strong\u003E combination would be reserved for patients with severe penicillin allergies where beta-lactam antibiotics cannot be used. This combination provides coverage for both gram-negative organisms (including \u003Cem\u003EPseudomonas\u003C/em\u003E) and MRSA, but is not first-line due to concerns about fluoroquinolone resistance.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAzithromycin\u003C/strong\u003E is a macrolide antibiotic primarily effective against atypical pathogens such as \u003Cem\u003EMycoplasma\u003C/em\u003E, \u003Cem\u003EChlamydia\u003C/em\u003E, and \u003Cem\u003ELegionella\u003C/em\u003E. It lacks activity against \u003Cem\u003EPseudomonas aeruginosa\u003C/em\u003E and other multidrug-resistant gram-negative organisms that are the primary concern in VAP.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAmoxicillin-clavulanate\u003C/strong\u003E is more appropriate for community-acquired pneumonia and lacks the anti-pseudomonal activity required for VAP. It would not provide adequate coverage against the resistant organisms typically encountered in the intensive care unit setting after prolonged mechanical ventilation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Ventilator-associated pneumonia (VAP) is defined as pneumonia occurring more than 48 hours after endotracheal intubation.","Gram-negative bacteria, particularly Pseudomonas aeruginosa, are common causative organisms in late-onset VAP.","Empiric antibiotic therapy for late-onset VAP should cover Pseudomonas aeruginosa and other multidrug-resistant organisms such as MRSA."],"references":["Papazian L, Klompas M, Luyt CE. Ventilator-associated pneumonia in adults: a narrative review. Intensive Care Med. 2020 May;46(5):888-906. doi: 10.1007/s00134-020-05980-0. Epub 2020 Mar 10. PMID: 32157357; PMCID: PMC7095206. Available from: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7095206/","Kohbodi GA, Rajasurya V, Noor A. Ventilator-Associated Pneumonia. 2023 Sep 4. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2025 Jan\u2013. PMID: 29939533. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29939533/","Koenig SM, Truwit JD. Ventilator-associated pneumonia: diagnosis, treatment, and prevention. Clin Microbiol Rev. 2006 Oct;19(4):637-57. doi: 10.1128/CMR.00051-05. PMID: 17041138; PMCID: PMC1592694. Available from: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC1592694/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86280"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14556"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86280","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/86280"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-05-27T18:04:47+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-27T18:04:48+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7249"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"103855"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"11","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory Medicine","synonyms":["Pulmonology"],"description":null,"position